                            <comment id="11280" author="lei" created="Wed, 4 Jan 2017 10:43:39 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried to stress pushing the requests to the extreme with 100K connections, it throws &quot;Illegal Instruction: 4&quot; in macOS terminal/console and have not tested with that amount of load testing. I believe it applicable for Kitura which it has happened in the earlier version few months ago but have not tried with the latest version&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;macOS 10.12, 8GB Memory RAM, has unused 500MB memory.&lt;br/&gt;
wrk -d1M -t4 -c100000 &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8181&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8181&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using project for the test, compiled with release mode and commented logging display printed on the console:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/PerfectExamples/Perfect-Turnstile-PostgreSQL-Demo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/PerfectExamples/Perfect-Turnstile-PostgreSQL-Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11281" author="lei" created="Wed, 4 Jan 2017 11:05:28 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;The error only happen once in a rare situation, if Perfect could be resilient and robust by auto restarting itself if the process was terminated by known error?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11282" author="lei" created="Wed, 4 Jan 2017 11:08:22 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I have found the error was caused by improper database configuration that lead to crash. Nothing to do with the system load.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
